My top spot for tasty pizza. Service is typically above par. This place has a good atmosphere. Reminds me of a cafe in Chicago I liked to visit.
Fine spot for quality Pizza. this place will surprise you. i will be bringing friends next time. this place has a great design.

The pizza and the food are delicious i really like the service i have received from this pizza lounge.

This is actually quite a cool place.  At the Downtown Pizza Lounge you get sort of a New York feel that really makes you think that you could have stepped into a place in Brooklyn.  This is a great place to go before or after a night where you hit the bars in the area and have your self a few drinks.
Fast service great pizza
One of the best pizza places I've eaten at, not too bad price wise either, overall amazing experience
$9 for two slices and a drink. Crust is crispy, cheese is pull apart stringy. Absolutely delicious and reasonable.
2 big slices of pizza and a soda for $9.  A good deal and a good slice of pizza.  I did not get any of the wings but I will return to give them a try as well.

A small restaurant in downtown Phoenix on the corner of Washington & 1st St. They offer slice pizza specials & I especially enjoyed their thin crust pepperoni. Great place to stop in before a game or show!

By far one of the best pizza places you can get a slice for at a decent price and a decent size
Delicious little pizza lounge. Really enjoyed the ambience and the pizza is delicious. Excellent variety of pizza. Wings available, too. Open business hours. Enjoy!
It was crazy hot the day we visited.. pizza is okay.. owner was kind to let us hang out for awhile

It's just okay, nothing special.  It is expensive, a small slice of Pizza for $5, add small salad and drink it's $10, but in my opinion not worth it.  I had to get one more slice just to fill me up, now I paid $15 all together.  I won't be going there again, there just isn't anything exciting about it.

Nice well done pizza

I have a kind of sensitive stomach, so if it was out for a long, long time I would be saying other wise. It's a small place with nice people. Great atmosphere! Middle of lunch rush during ComiCon and I was still in and out with my slice in record time!

Great location. Walking distances from close offices. Really quick service and excellent pizza for the price point. They play soccer matches so that great!

surprised thin pizza was so good, and they serve beer...

Love the pizza here, and the #1 is a great deal
Decent thin crust, nothing too special. Must get really busy after big games, as it caters to the sports crowd.

I never review places....like ever, but this is my new go to lunch spot downtown. Being from New England finding good pizza in AZ is tough. Great pizza, great wings, fast and pleasant service, and even clean restrooms. These guys know what …
Fast service at a fair price. Nothing great quality wise so you get what you pay for.
Nice pizza, nice deals!
Food was great and service was fast.

I really liked the pizza for a "by the slice" type place. And the super nice guy behind the counter gave me a military discount as well when he noticed my Military ID card in my wallet. What a nice touch! I'll definitely be back.

The pizza is really, really good! It was a huge slice for the $4 and some change I paid. The service was okay. I had to initiate the sale and the cashier said maybe two words. But the pizza was good and it was fast. A friendlier employee would have made this a 5 star.
Great wings, amazing pizza! Guy behind the counter is really cool!
Food delicious and atmosphere is great. Right downtown. Only complaint is price. $4 for a slice of pizza just doesn't seem right, even if it does taste so good.
Fantastic pizza, full pie or by the slice.

Good place for a quick lunch. The pizza is good and the wings are delicious. Ask for a mix of the honey with the hot. Affordable and fast.
Very good pizza with several varieties prepared. They have a basic selection of fountain drinks. The atmosphere is very casual and feels relaxed.
Pizza was delish!!
Helped me out in a time of dire need! Thx!

The pizza crust is so good and the cheese is stringy

Good place to go when there are ball games in town

This place is amazing! I was staying at a local hotel and needed a quick bite so I stopped at DPL. This place exceeded my expectations w/ their great food, good staff & decent pricing! There's so much competition downtown but you can't go wrong here..:)
Great pizza, different pizza it stands out from the usual slice.

I was shocked to find out there were no reviews for this fantastic pizzeria! This is basically Brooklyn NYC Pizza since it's the same owner and it is beyond delicious!!! If you love thin crust, New York style "pie" and you're in the downtown area, look no further than D T's!
